title: Hohenfels wins third straight, grabs playoff spot
text:
Hohenfels wins third straight, grabs playoff spot Naples page 
NAPLES, Italy -- The Hohenfels Tigers rattled off their third straight victory and clinched a playoff berth Saturday wtih a 20-0 defeat of the host Naples Wildcats. 
Tony Saintmelus was the star again, providing all three Hohenfels scores in the game. He caught a 22-yard touchdown in the second quarter, ran in a 42-yard score in the fourth and returned an interception 46 yards for six insurance points in the game's final minutes. 
Saintmelus finished with 110 rushing yards on 19 carries and six catches for 89 yards. Quarterback Orcun Selmani completed 10 passes for 89 yards through the air. 
Kelly Jordan made five tackles and a sack for the Tiger defense. 
Naples freshman quarterback Javonte West completed seven passes for 73 yards and rushed 12 times for another 51 yards. Teammate Karrington Evans caught four passes for 63 yards. 
The 3-1 Tigers have been on a tear since their opening-weekend loss to Bitburg. They'll play for postseason positioning next weekend against Vicenza. 
The winless Wildcats are out of playoff contention, though they might find themselves in a position to spoil things for rival Aviano next weekend. Join the conversation and share your voice.
